      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THAT'S OKAY (2) goes very well this trip starting 23 times for nine wins and four minors. Was out of placings last time (18.02) at this track in a Grade 3/4, finishing fifth and beaten 6 lengths. Looks the one to beat with even luck. DYNAMIC AUSSIE (6) turned in a plain run last time when seventh at this track over 525m behind Malicious (31.35) in a Grade 4/5. Has the ability to give this a shake. ROCKY GALVIN (7) was drawn the middle last start but pinged the lids and recorded an all-the-way win (17.60) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Should feature again. LUNA ZEAL (1) can fill a top-three spot.",
